I've created a new folder at \.cursor\project_context

The purpose of the folder is to store context on the performed work in different chats, but that can be helpful when working on a new, or updating existing feature, or trying to fix bugs. 

The ides is to create a separate file per session, so it's easier to find relevant information.

At the same time, if we are working on a feature in multiple session, the naming of the files should be the same and appended by a number to see continuity.

For example:
- Monday, May 24, 2025 - Implementing solution to persisten conversation id throughout the same user session [1]
- Monday, May 25, 2025 - Implementing solution to persisten conversation id throughout the same user session [2]
- Monday, May 25, 2025 - Implementing solution to persisten conversation id throughout the same user session [3]
- Monday, May 26, 2025 - Implementing solution to persisten conversation id throughout the same user session [4]
- Monday, May 26, 2025 - Implementing solution to persisten conversation id throughout the same user session [5]

Make sure to use keywords that will be relevant during subsequent searches that can include:
- file names changed, and summary of changes and why
- related feature that this was for
- specific problem and solution of a bug
- etc.

In order to keep the context smaller, if the change is small, instead of creating a new file, you can UPDATE the latest existing file, with updated changed or even overwrite text if it was for a wrong solution